headline: Gov't shutdown could have lasting effects on airlines. Here's why.
summary: The airline industry could see long-term impacts from the government shutdown, Raymond James managing director Savi Syth tells Yahoo Finance. Syth explains that while the government is shut down, there isn't air traffic controller training, another headwind for a workforce that is already in short supply. Also catch what Hickory Global Partners president Chris Dane has to say about shutdown pressures airline operators could be faced with, all this coming after Delta Air Lines (DAL) topped third quarter earnings estimates. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Market Domination.

headline: What could push airlines to tipping point if US shutdown drags on
summary: Delta Air Lines (DAL) stock is lifting off on Thursday after topping third quarter estimates: revenue of $15.2 billion (vs. estimates of $15.1 billion) and adjusted earnings of $1.71 per share (vs. estimates of $1.56). As the US government's shutdown moves into its ninth day, what sort of disruptions could airline operators see in the coming days if the shutdown drags on longer? Hickory Global Partners president and managing partner Chris Dane and Yahoo Finance senior reporter Pras Subramanian weigh in. Yahoo Finance senior reporter Pras Subramanian
